    title: 'Demolition Services Jacksonville FL',
    metaTitle: 'Demolition Services Jacksonville FL - Licensed Contractors',
    metaDescription: 'How much does demolition cost in Jacksonville FL? 904 Dumpster handles residential, commercial, interior, pool, and site-clearing demolition with permits, asbestos surveys, and debris hauling included. Free on-site estimates.',
    quickAnswer: 'Demolition services in Jacksonville, FL cover residential, commercial, interior, pool, mobile-home, shed/deck, and site-clearing teardowns. Industry guides put residential demolition costs in the $644 to $1,000 range for kitchen and bathroom interior work, and $4,000 to $25,000 for full-structure removal depending on square footage. 904 Dumpster handles permits through the City of Jacksonville Building Inspection Division, the asbestos survey required on any structure built before 1978, and debris hauling at Trail Ridge Landfill, all bundled into a single fixed-price quote with no broker markup.',
    bodyContentTitle: 'How Much Does Demolition Cost in Jacksonville and What is Included',
    bodyContent: `<h3>What types of demolition services are available in Jacksonville</h3><p>Demolition in Jacksonville covers a wide range of project scopes, and the right type depends on what is coming down. <strong>Interior demolition</strong> is selective gut-out of finish materials (cabinets, flooring, drywall, fixtures) inside a structure that stays standing, common on kitchen and bathroom remodels. <strong>Residential demolition</strong> is full structure removal of single-family homes, common in teardown-and-rebuild infill projects across older Jacksonville neighborhoods. <strong>Commercial demolition</strong> is structure removal of office buildings, retail spaces, warehouses, or restaurants. <strong>Pool demolition</strong> handles in-ground concrete and gunite pool removal plus the surrounding decking. <strong>Mobile-home demolition</strong> covers older single-wide and double-wide manufactured-home removal. <strong>Site clearing</strong> covers brush, trees, fencing, and small-structure removal to prepare a lot for new construction. 904 Dumpster handles the residential, commercial, interior, pool, mobile-home, and shed/deck categories.</p><h3>How much does residential demolition cost in Jacksonville</h3><p>Residential demolition in Jacksonville varies widely depending on the scope. Industry pricing guides put typical kitchen or bathroom interior demolition between $644 and $1,000, with $800 as a reasonable mid-range. Full-structure single-family home demolition runs $4,000 to $25,000 depending on square footage, foundation type, and access constraints. Pool removal runs $4,000 to $15,000 depending on pool size, fill type (full removal vs filled-in-place), and whether decking comes with it. Shed and deck demolition is usually $300 to $1,500 same-day. The 904 Dumpster demolition quote bundles labor, permits, asbestos survey when required, debris hauling, and disposal at Trail Ridge Landfill into a single fixed price, so the number on the estimate is the number on the invoice.</p><h3>Permits and asbestos surveys for Jacksonville demolition</h3><p>Almost every demolition project in Jacksonville requires a permit from the <a href="https://www.jacksonville.gov/departments/planning-and-development/building-inspection-division" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Jacksonville Building Inspection Division</a>. Interior demolition permits typically run 5 to 10 business days; full-structure residential demolition permits take longer because the city verifies utility disconnects and notifies neighboring property owners before issuing the permit. Layered on top of that: any structure built before 1978 needs an asbestos survey under <a href="https://floridadep.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Florida Department of Environmental Protection</a> rules, and any positive sample requires a licensed asbestos abatement contractor before demolition can proceed. 904 Dumpster handles the permit submission and the asbestos survey ordering as part of the demolition price, which avoids the most common project delay.</p><h3>Cheapest demolition options for small Jacksonville projects</h3><p>The cheapest demolition projects in the Jacksonville market are usually shed, deck, and small-outbuilding removals where there is no permit, no asbestos survey, and no utility disconnect required. Those typically run $300 to $1,500 same-day. The next tier is interior selective demolition (a single bathroom gut-out, a kitchen tear-out without changing footprint), which runs $644 to $1,500 typical. Full residential demolition and pool removal are higher-cost categories because of permits, hauling volume, and the equipment required. For homeowners trying to minimize demolition cost in Jacksonville, the practical levers are: scope tightly to the work that actually matters, schedule outside hurricane season when contractor demand drops, and bundle the demolition with the debris hauling rather than splitting them across two vendors. 904 Dumpster bundles both, so there is no separate dumpster contract to negotiate after the demo crew leaves.</p><h3>Pool demolition and removal in Jacksonville</h3><p>Pool demolition is one of the more frequently requested 904 Dumpster demolition services because Jacksonville has a high concentration of older in-ground pools across <strong>Mandarin</strong>, <strong>San Marco</strong>, <a href="/dumpster-rental-fleming-island-fl">Fleming Island</a>, and <a href="/dumpster-rental-ponte-vedra-fl">Ponte Vedra</a>. There are two common methods. <strong>Full removal</strong> breaks out the pool shell entirely, hauls the concrete and rebar off-site (concrete goes to a recycling crusher, see our <a href="/concrete-disposal-dumpster-jacksonville-fl">concrete disposal dumpster</a> service for the hauling side), and backfills with clean fill. Full removal preserves the buildable area on the lot but costs more. <strong>Filled-in-place</strong> leaves the broken-up pool shell at the bottom of the hole, fills with engineered fill, and compacts. It costs less but the lot is no longer buildable in that footprint. Most Jacksonville pool removals are residential and the customer's choice depends on whether they plan to put a structure or addition on top of the old pool location.</p><h3>Site clearing, mobile-home removal, and commercial structure demolition</h3><p>Beyond residential interior and pool work, 904 Dumpster handles site clearing for new construction (brush, trees, small outbuildings, old fencing), mobile-home demolition for older single-wide and double-wide units common in rural Clay and Nassau counties, and commercial structure demolition for retail, office, and light-industrial buildings. Commercial demolition typically pairs with longer permit timelines, OSHA safety planning, and sometimes phased takedowns where the structure has to come down without disturbing adjacent occupied buildings. Site clearing and mobile-home work are usually faster (1 to 3 days) and lower cost. For projects that involve substantial concrete punch-out (driveway, foundation, slab, pool), pair the demolition with our <a href="/concrete-disposal-dumpster-jacksonville-fl">concrete disposal dumpster</a> for the heavy-debris hauling side. For broader debris hauling without the demo labor, see our <a href="/construction-dumpster-rental-jacksonville-fl">construction dumpster rental</a> service.</p>`,
